  snap_fwd: GACA (will be on 5' end of PCR product)
  snap_rev: CTCA (will be on 5' end of PCR product, RC on 3' end)

Expected assembly order and junctions:
  1. input backbone
     3' overhang: TCAT -> will ligate to ATGA
  2. egfp (no stop)
     5' overhang: ATGA
     3' overhang: TACC -> will ligate to GGTA
  3. flag (no start/stop)
     5' overhang: GGTA
     3' overhang: TGAA -> will ligate to GACA
  4. snap (no start)
     5' overhang: GACA
     3' overhang: CTCA -> will ligate to TGAG
  -> back to input backbone
     5' overhang: TGAG

✓ Assembly design is correct for circular plasmid formation!
